WEBVTT

00:10.635 --> 00:12.637
[wind gently blowing]

00:18.560 --> 00:20.562
[gentle music plays]

00:20.645 --> 00:22.147
[water bubbling]

00:26.651 --> 00:27.652
[Arnold] My whole life,

00:28.653 --> 00:29.612
I had this

00:30.697 --> 00:32.699
unusual talent

00:34.242 --> 00:37.120
that I could see things very clearly

00:37.203 --> 00:38.121
in front of me.

00:41.666 --> 00:42.834
If I can see it,

00:43.334 --> 00:44.961
then it must be achievable.

00:51.176 --> 00:52.802
The idea was

00:52.886 --> 00:55.096
to sculpt the body

00:55.180 --> 00:56.181
to your will.

01:03.480 --> 01:04.814
[audience cheering]

01:06.149 --> 01:08.693
But it also can be used
to shape your mind,

01:11.196 --> 01:14.449
to do the things
that everyone calls impossible.

01:16.451 --> 01:19.913
And that gives you the will…

01:20.580 --> 01:21.414
I'll be back.

01:21.998 --> 01:23.750
…and no doubt

01:24.876 --> 01:27.337
that you can make your visions,

01:27.420 --> 01:29.172
not only become a reality,

01:31.716 --> 01:33.384
but go beyond your dreams.

01:36.096 --> 01:37.972
I had a fire in the belly

01:38.056 --> 01:39.349
for much more.

01:40.183 --> 01:42.936
Much, much more.

01:43.436 --> 01:45.438
[upbeat music plays]

01:49.484 --> 01:52.320
[man] If I had to describe Arnold
in one word,

01:52.403 --> 01:54.948
I would say
he's the most calculating individual

01:55.031 --> 01:56.783
that I've ever come across.

01:57.826 --> 02:01.037
He's the most competitive maniac
I've ever met.

02:01.746 --> 02:03.665
[woman] He is, just, magic.

02:03.748 --> 02:06.292
If Arnold is showing up on set,

02:06.376 --> 02:08.002
you better up your game.

02:09.254 --> 02:12.006
[man] We couldn't even stand
to breathe the same air.

02:12.090 --> 02:14.425
He broke every damn rule there was.

02:16.427 --> 02:20.140
[woman 2] Arnold believed that a crisis
is a terrible thing to waste.

02:20.682 --> 02:23.059
[man 2] Arnold sold Arnold.

02:23.726 --> 02:25.812
[man 3] He gets the joke of the universe.

02:25.895 --> 02:27.105
[Arnold laughing]

02:28.731 --> 02:29.649
Bullshit.

02:38.116 --> 02:40.118
[drumroll]

02:41.911 --> 02:44.414
[announcer]
Ladies and gentlemen, from Austria,

02:44.497 --> 02:48.001
welcome to our stage, please,
Mr. Arnold Schwarzenegger.

02:48.084 --> 02:49.043
[cheering and applause]

02:49.127 --> 02:51.671
[announcer 2] Look now,
Arnold Schwarzenegger, 22 years of age.

02:51.754 --> 02:53.298
Now living in Los Angeles.

02:54.924 --> 02:57.010
Weighs almost 230 pounds.

02:57.093 --> 02:59.345
He works out several hours a day.

02:59.429 --> 03:01.639
This is his life. He's a professional.

03:01.723 --> 03:03.933
When he's not doing this,
he'll be touring the world,

03:04.017 --> 03:05.393
putting on exhibitions.

03:06.728 --> 03:08.730
Listen to that crowd react to him.

03:08.813 --> 03:10.815
[cheering and applause]

03:18.072 --> 03:19.407
And there you have it!

03:20.074 --> 03:22.368
Arnold Schwarzenegger from Austria.

03:23.036 --> 03:26.915
Seven judges observe specific points
of muscular development and presentation.

03:27.498 --> 03:30.251
[announcer] In position number one,

03:30.752 --> 03:32.712
Mr. Arnold Schwarzenegger.

03:32.795 --> 03:34.047
[announcer 2] And the winner!

03:34.130 --> 03:35.840
What a big day for this youngster.

03:35.924 --> 03:39.052
[Arnold] When I was in school already,
I felt like I didn't belong here.

03:39.135 --> 03:40.678
I belonged somewhere else.

03:41.346 --> 03:44.974
That's not the life I want to live,
like the Austrians live their life,

03:45.058 --> 03:46.684
which is, you know,

03:46.768 --> 03:50.063
go to school until 18
and get married, have kids.

03:50.146 --> 03:52.148
Just work to support your family.

03:52.690 --> 03:56.861
I thought that my purpose for life
was just far beyond that.

04:01.449 --> 04:03.451
[calm music plays]

04:12.710 --> 04:14.712
[Arnold] I always liked coming back here.

04:15.505 --> 04:18.841
Each time you come,
you look from a different point of view,

04:18.925 --> 04:21.052
through a different lens.

04:22.929 --> 04:25.932
It was very important,
every time I came to Austria,

04:26.015 --> 04:28.559
even to promote my movies or bodybuilding,

04:28.643 --> 04:29.644
or whatever…

04:29.727 --> 04:31.938
I always came back down here to Thal.

04:32.855 --> 04:37.110
I think it's always good to stay in touch
with your roots and where you come from.

04:37.193 --> 04:38.569
[church bells ringing]

04:38.653 --> 04:41.322
Thal is a beautiful, beautiful place.

04:42.282 --> 04:43.116
[cows moo]

04:43.199 --> 04:44.701
The house where I grew up

04:45.576 --> 04:47.161
was surrounded by farms.

04:49.247 --> 04:51.833
We had a castle across the street,

04:51.916 --> 04:53.793
built in the 1100s.

04:53.876 --> 04:57.171
So this was our playground.
So it was absolutely beautiful.

05:00.091 --> 05:01.884
Our house was an old house.

05:03.052 --> 05:06.180
It was built in the beginning of 1800s.

05:07.473 --> 05:09.642
Downstairs lived the forest ranger.

05:10.560 --> 05:13.229
We had the upstairs of that old house.

05:14.564 --> 05:16.232
[speaking German]

05:28.703 --> 05:30.955
My mother was hardworking.

05:32.206 --> 05:33.374
Aurelia.

05:34.959 --> 05:37.503
She would never, ever pull back.

05:38.921 --> 05:41.799
She was a cleanliness fanatic.

05:42.467 --> 05:45.219
I'm telling you, she was on her knees

05:45.303 --> 05:46.220
twice a week,

05:46.304 --> 05:48.431
scrubbing the floor.

05:49.474 --> 05:52.352
And then, when you open up the cabinet

05:52.435 --> 05:53.478
with the towels,

05:53.561 --> 05:55.646
it was perfectly placed.

05:56.939 --> 05:57.982
There was an edge.

05:58.566 --> 06:00.026
Bang. Bang. Bang.

06:03.571 --> 06:06.115
If my father would touch that,

06:06.199 --> 06:07.492
she would go nuts.

06:08.701 --> 06:10.536
This is what a fanatic she was.

06:12.580 --> 06:15.750
Growing up, I'll tell you what I learned.

06:15.833 --> 06:17.251
"Work your ass off."

06:18.336 --> 06:21.547
My father was the chief
of the country police.

06:22.465 --> 06:25.343
He was a tyrant
and a very tough police officer.

06:25.426 --> 06:27.136
There was no screwing around.

06:27.970 --> 06:31.224
My dad thought they should create
some discipline in the house.

06:31.307 --> 06:33.393
He said you have to earn breakfast.

06:38.564 --> 06:41.067
I had a very good relationship
with my brother,

06:41.150 --> 06:43.403
but it was a competitive relationship.

06:43.945 --> 06:46.114
I mean, he was a year older, my brother.

06:46.197 --> 06:48.032
More muscular, smarter.

06:48.116 --> 06:50.159
He was very good in school.

06:50.660 --> 06:53.788
My father also made us
compete against each other.

06:54.497 --> 06:55.957
Who runs faster?

06:56.040 --> 07:00.044
Who picks more beautiful flowers
on Mother's Day?

07:01.671 --> 07:04.132
My father says, "I'll give you one hour."

07:06.008 --> 07:08.052
My brother would come home
with his flowers.

07:08.136 --> 07:11.597
My father says,
"Meinhard, good boy. Very, very good."

07:11.681 --> 07:14.016
"Arnold, next year you will try it again."

07:14.100 --> 07:17.186
So it was competitive.
Even stupid things like that.

07:20.606 --> 07:23.484
My father gave me that drive
he gave me that fire in the belly,

07:23.568 --> 07:25.111
and then with the message,

07:25.820 --> 07:27.321
"Whatever you do, Arnold,

07:28.865 --> 07:29.699
be useful."

07:35.496 --> 07:40.001
The way I grew up, it was very tough,
even though it was beautiful countryside.

07:40.084 --> 07:42.253
But to grow up after a war…

07:45.756 --> 07:47.467
What happens to your head

07:47.550 --> 07:49.177
when you come home from war

07:49.260 --> 07:52.513
suffering
the post-traumatic stress syndrome,

07:52.597 --> 07:53.681
like my father?

07:54.557 --> 07:58.561
He was buried underneath buildings,
rubble, for three days,

08:00.271 --> 08:02.523
and on top of that, they lost the war.

08:03.357 --> 08:05.193
They went home so depressed.

08:06.235 --> 08:09.572
Austria was a country of broken men.

08:09.655 --> 08:11.657
[somber music plays]

08:13.159 --> 08:17.413
I think there were times
when my father really struggled.

08:18.581 --> 08:20.041
When we got smacked,

08:21.042 --> 08:23.836
or my father would use the belt
and hit us.

08:23.920 --> 08:26.756
The kid next door was hit also
by his father.

08:26.839 --> 08:29.509
Everyone was going through the same thing.

08:32.094 --> 08:33.346
As I was getting older,

08:33.429 --> 08:36.349
and the more I read stuff
about the outside world,

08:36.432 --> 08:39.560
outside of Austria,
the more I started feeling like,

08:39.644 --> 08:42.230
"I don't think that I was brought up
in the right place."

08:42.313 --> 08:43.773
"There's something off here."

08:45.816 --> 08:49.028
And I know this sounds crazy,
but for a while,

08:49.529 --> 08:54.116
I thought,
"Maybe my dad isn't really my dad."

08:55.201 --> 08:57.286
"Maybe it's some American soldier."

09:04.835 --> 09:08.047
I checked into it.
I said, "Where does this come from?"

09:08.130 --> 09:10.925
"My desire that I really

09:12.051 --> 09:13.553
maybe don't belong to Austria?"

09:13.636 --> 09:16.055
"Maybe I belong to America. Why is that?"

09:17.014 --> 09:20.476
That convicted me
that one day I have to be over there.

09:20.560 --> 09:22.061
I'm in the wrong place.

09:23.771 --> 09:25.314
"I gotta get out of here."

09:25.398 --> 09:27.400
[adventurous music plays]

09:28.734 --> 09:32.572
When my brother and I went
to town in Graz…

09:35.032 --> 09:37.994
that was the first time
we had exposure to the city.

09:39.245 --> 09:42.456
After school, kind of walked around
in town a little bit

09:42.540 --> 09:44.125
and we saw the movie theaters.

09:44.208 --> 09:46.294
This ad that was out there in front

09:46.377 --> 09:48.504
of this guy standing like this.

09:48.588 --> 09:51.215
I was kind of, like, in a trance.

09:51.924 --> 09:52.842
Who is that?

09:52.925 --> 09:54.510
[majestic music plays]

09:54.594 --> 09:57.305
[movie narrator]
Hercules and the Captive Women.

09:57.388 --> 09:58.472
Here at last,

09:58.556 --> 10:01.225
with a new and dynamic personality.

10:01.309 --> 10:03.728
Reg Park as Hercules.

10:05.021 --> 10:05.980
Superhuman strength.

10:06.063 --> 10:08.357
[Arnold]
I went in there and I saw this body,

10:08.441 --> 10:13.195
and I was so amazed at this body
that I could not get it out of my mind.

10:14.113 --> 10:16.240
The testosterone was kicking in.

10:16.824 --> 10:19.410
Getting interested in girls
was kicking in.

10:19.493 --> 10:21.203
Everything started happening.

10:22.163 --> 10:25.458
And then I walked by a store.

10:26.417 --> 10:28.419
There was all this American stuff.

10:29.253 --> 10:32.256
One of the things was
muscle magazines from America.

10:32.340 --> 10:34.342
This guy Reg Park

10:34.425 --> 10:35.885
who I saw in the movies,

10:35.968 --> 10:37.428
he's on the cover.

10:37.511 --> 10:40.431
Inside, it has his training program.

10:40.514 --> 10:43.059
He was up at 5:00 in the morning.
He was training.

10:43.142 --> 10:45.936
And then he was training a second time.
And then a third time.

10:46.020 --> 10:47.271
I have to do that.

10:48.147 --> 10:50.483
It said how he became Mr. Universe

10:51.275 --> 10:55.446
and how he was discovered in Rome
to become Hercules.

10:56.405 --> 10:58.240
So I said, "Oh my God."

10:58.324 --> 10:59.867
"This guy is my idol."

10:59.950 --> 11:03.204
So he was kind of like my blueprint

11:04.246 --> 11:05.706
to where I want to go in life.

11:14.674 --> 11:18.552
My drive to come to America was enormous.

11:19.637 --> 11:22.264
And if you're willing to put
the hours behind it,

11:22.348 --> 11:24.850
then you have to really find out
what is it,

11:24.934 --> 11:27.228
where your talent lies.

11:27.311 --> 11:28.437
Where are you good at?

11:29.021 --> 11:33.401
To me, bodybuilding represented
a sport that is American.

11:33.484 --> 11:35.736
The feedback that I got in the gym
was enormous,

11:35.820 --> 11:39.281
so that's why I knew
this is the direction that I wanted to go.

11:45.871 --> 11:49.375
I would be working out in my house.

11:49.917 --> 11:51.335
There was no sound.

11:51.419 --> 11:52.253
Nothing.

11:53.921 --> 11:55.089
[breathing deeply]

11:57.091 --> 11:59.802
And I could think and concentrate

11:59.885 --> 12:03.347
and visualize how I'm gonna become
a bodybuilding champion.

12:04.640 --> 12:06.642
How I'm gonna move to America.

12:06.726 --> 12:08.728
How I'm gonna get into the movies.

12:08.811 --> 12:11.147
How I'm gonna make millions of dollars.

12:11.230 --> 12:13.232
["Marmor, Stein und Eisen bricht" plays]

12:15.651 --> 12:20.030
[Arnold] The Thalersee, the lake,
was a magical scene.

12:20.656 --> 12:23.284
Hanging out with professional wrestlers,

12:23.367 --> 12:24.577
weightlifters,

12:24.660 --> 12:25.870
bodybuilders,

12:25.953 --> 12:27.163
people with muscles.

12:28.831 --> 12:30.416
I met Mr. Austria,

12:30.499 --> 12:31.542
Kurt Marnul,

12:31.625 --> 12:34.170
and walking around
with these nice-looking girls

12:34.253 --> 12:36.630
and pulling up
in his little Alfa Romeo sports car.

12:37.506 --> 12:39.216
I found this very impressive.

12:40.468 --> 12:42.970
I just all the sudden
became part of that clique.

12:43.053 --> 12:45.848
I was like the young kid
that they were adopting.

12:45.931 --> 12:47.933
[music continues in German]

13:00.654 --> 13:01.947
♪ Everybody now ♪

13:02.031 --> 13:06.076
[Arnold] I think, ever since then,
I kind of celebrated this camaraderie.

13:06.160 --> 13:10.206
And because I admired it so much,
I created that no matter where I went.

13:11.749 --> 13:13.209
[music fades]

13:14.168 --> 13:18.297
My father was negative, because it
was not the typical thing to do.

13:18.380 --> 13:21.801
The typical thing to do
is you become a soccer player

13:22.718 --> 13:25.763
or you become a ski champion.

13:25.846 --> 13:27.306
This is Austrian.

13:27.389 --> 13:29.642
What the hell are you doing
with weightlifting?

13:29.725 --> 13:31.977
And you're looking in the mirror
when you train.

13:32.061 --> 13:33.562
What is that all about?

13:33.646 --> 13:35.940
[speaking German]

13:38.234 --> 13:40.110
Which means, like, into yourself.

13:40.194 --> 13:43.739
He says, "If you want to use your muscles,
go chop wood."

13:48.410 --> 13:50.538
And my mother got freaked out.

13:51.539 --> 13:52.915
"All his friends,

13:53.833 --> 13:55.835
they have, you know,

13:57.002 --> 13:59.797
girls above their bed."

14:01.173 --> 14:04.301
"My son doesn't have one girl up here.
Look at that."

14:04.385 --> 14:08.180
"Not one girl.
I mean, it's only naked men oiled up."

14:08.764 --> 14:10.432
"Where did we do wrong?"

14:14.353 --> 14:17.064
[man in German] In the beginning,
Arnold wasn't a leader.

14:17.147 --> 14:19.525
He adapted to us.

14:19.608 --> 14:22.027
But within a year,

14:22.111 --> 14:25.281
I think he gained 15.2 kilos.

14:26.657 --> 14:29.618
When you're in Arnold's company,

14:29.702 --> 14:32.872
you get the impression
that everything is easy

14:32.955 --> 14:34.498
and there are no problems.

14:35.791 --> 14:39.461
My father often came along,

14:39.545 --> 14:42.464
and he recognized Arnold's potential.

14:46.677 --> 14:48.679
[Arnold in English] Freddy Gerstl,
the father, became

14:48.762 --> 14:50.639
kind of like a real big supporter.

14:52.474 --> 14:54.852
He said, "You have to have
not only just the strong muscles,

14:54.935 --> 14:58.022
like you guys are doing,
but also you have to have a strong mind."

14:58.814 --> 15:03.736
The body doesn't operate by itself.
It operates because you give it direction.

15:04.361 --> 15:05.988
He says, "Remember one thing."

15:06.071 --> 15:10.242
"That you can get an injury,
and then all the athletic stuff is over.

15:11.327 --> 15:13.621
"You can have millions of dollars."

15:13.704 --> 15:16.540
"Someone can rob you blind,
and it's gone."

15:16.624 --> 15:19.710
"But the only thing no one can take
is your mind."

15:19.793 --> 15:21.045
"Your brain power."

15:22.004 --> 15:23.714
"Your mind, your will,

15:23.797 --> 15:26.759
is, in the end,
much more important than the body."

15:28.802 --> 15:32.806
He was the father figure
quite the opposite from my father.

15:33.515 --> 15:35.893
Unlike my father,
who criticized everything,

15:35.976 --> 15:39.521
that guy was more the understanding father

15:39.605 --> 15:43.108
that understood and he kind of smoothly
would you in the right direction,

15:43.192 --> 15:44.401
rather than forcing you.

15:44.485 --> 15:47.071
I always hear this voice behind me saying,

15:47.154 --> 15:48.822
"Be hungry for information."

15:50.199 --> 15:52.201
[church bells ringing]

15:52.743 --> 15:57.206
[Arnold] I joined the weight lifting club
called Athletik Union Graz.

15:57.706 --> 16:01.460
The guys from the lake
also were training there.

16:01.543 --> 16:04.672
So I could train,
finally, with the big boys.

16:05.255 --> 16:07.216
That's where Kurt Marnul was training.

16:08.258 --> 16:10.970
This weightlifting club
became, for me, the mecca.

16:12.054 --> 16:13.973
I became addicted to that,

16:14.056 --> 16:15.516
and so I went every day.

16:15.599 --> 16:17.810
[action music plays]

16:20.688 --> 16:24.024
When I walked into the gym,
there was this wall

16:24.817 --> 16:25.818
that was wood.

16:26.443 --> 16:28.570
And then I would just take a chalk

16:29.488 --> 16:30.823
and I would write down

16:31.740 --> 16:32.700
bizeps,

16:33.450 --> 16:34.702
trizeps,

16:34.785 --> 16:37.371
brust, rücken.

16:40.207 --> 16:43.127
So I would do a set of biceps curls.

16:43.210 --> 16:44.253
[grunts]

16:44.962 --> 16:47.673
Then I would write down next to this,
one line.

16:48.507 --> 16:52.052
Then I would put another line
and then another line and another line.

16:52.761 --> 16:54.054
Then, the next one.

16:54.138 --> 16:55.973
Flies on the bench.

16:56.056 --> 16:57.099
[grunts]

16:57.182 --> 16:59.476
And I'd know when I did my 20 sets

16:59.560 --> 17:01.103
of a specific exercise.

17:02.521 --> 17:04.481
Now after three hours of training,

17:04.565 --> 17:07.359
this whole thing would be
full of sets that I've done…

17:07.443 --> 17:08.277
[grunts]

17:08.360 --> 17:10.404
…to get to that goal that I want go.

17:12.906 --> 17:14.908
["Move It" plays]

17:15.659 --> 17:16.702
♪ Oh yeah ♪

17:17.536 --> 17:18.412
♪ Well now… ♪

17:21.331 --> 17:25.044
[Arnold] The bodybuilding, there was,
like, maybe, one or two events a year.

17:26.086 --> 17:28.881
Sometimes there were more
than one competition a day.

17:28.964 --> 17:32.217
Like, Mr. Steíermark,
which means Mr. Styria.

17:34.845 --> 17:37.473
And then there would be
the Mr. Hercules competition,

17:37.556 --> 17:40.851
which is usually for the guy
that was the most muscular.

17:43.145 --> 17:46.398
They would hire a local band
that was really, like, hot.

17:47.483 --> 17:51.445
They would have women
who were from some exotic place

17:51.528 --> 17:54.823
to give the sport of bodybuilding
a better reputation.

17:55.991 --> 17:58.035
Then, there would be
a Mr. Austria competition,

17:58.118 --> 18:00.412
which is, of course,
the national championships.

18:02.998 --> 18:04.166
♪ Whoo! ♪

18:06.085 --> 18:07.711
[birds chirping]

18:08.420 --> 18:10.547
[Arnold] This was a place
where I spent a lot of time,

18:10.631 --> 18:13.050
right here in this bed and in this room.

18:13.926 --> 18:16.637
So I would be just literally,
you know, lying here

18:17.137 --> 18:18.263
like this.

18:19.473 --> 18:21.642
And just, you know,
hanging here like this

18:22.476 --> 18:23.852
and dreaming.

18:25.229 --> 18:28.482
And then looking up at those characters.

18:30.609 --> 18:31.860
And then sitting up.

18:34.655 --> 18:37.407
I would see Reg Park,
you know, with his body,

18:38.075 --> 18:40.994
and then remembering the story

18:41.620 --> 18:44.039
of him growing up in Leeds,

18:44.123 --> 18:45.040
in England.

18:45.624 --> 18:47.292
The town was like Graz.

18:47.376 --> 18:48.752
It was a factory town.

18:49.336 --> 18:51.130
And the people worked hard.

18:51.213 --> 18:53.924
And I said to myself,
"He made it out of that?"

18:55.467 --> 18:57.761
"Then there's a chance for me also

18:57.845 --> 18:59.263
to make it out of here."

18:59.763 --> 19:04.393
Then you just look at any opportunity
you could have to get out of here.

19:04.476 --> 19:08.397
So I think that's the reason
I enlisted in the military early.

19:12.776 --> 19:16.530
In Austria,
everyone serves in the military.

19:17.990 --> 19:20.409
I decided to go at the age of 18.

19:21.451 --> 19:24.580
I wanted to finish my service
and then move on,

19:24.663 --> 19:26.957
because you could not get your passport

19:27.040 --> 19:29.710
unless you have done
your military service.

19:31.170 --> 19:35.007
I wanted to specialize in tank division
and to become a tank driver.

19:36.133 --> 19:38.677
They said that's impossible. I'm too tall.

19:40.429 --> 19:42.556
My father knew
a few people in the military,

19:42.639 --> 19:44.224
so I became a tank driver.

19:44.308 --> 19:48.228
Then I became the ballsiest tank driver
that they had.

19:49.271 --> 19:51.273
[military music plays]

19:55.110 --> 19:57.112
[soldiers marching]

19:59.865 --> 20:01.700
[Arnold] In the middle of basic training,

20:01.783 --> 20:06.788
I got the invitation to go
to this competition in Stuttgart, Germany.

20:06.872 --> 20:10.542
European's best-built man,
in the junior division.

20:10.626 --> 20:12.794
When I asked them, Can I go?"
they said no.

20:12.878 --> 20:14.254
[men counting]

20:14.338 --> 20:15.631
I did not realize

20:15.714 --> 20:17.883
that when you're in the middle
of the basic training,

20:17.966 --> 20:19.635
you are not allowed to leave.

20:22.346 --> 20:23.180
I went anyway.

20:24.097 --> 20:26.099
[romantic adventure music]

20:36.610 --> 20:38.612
[Arnold] Twenty-eight guys on the stage,

20:39.571 --> 20:40.864
and I win.

20:48.121 --> 20:50.123
I saw my career in front of me.

20:51.625 --> 20:54.795
I saw myself on that Mr. Universe stage.

20:56.505 --> 20:59.049
I just had to replace Reg Park's head,

20:59.132 --> 21:02.302
put my head on it,
and stand there with the trophy

21:02.386 --> 21:03.887
and flex my muscles.

21:03.971 --> 21:05.013
And I saw

21:05.514 --> 21:07.057
the thousands of people

21:08.267 --> 21:11.603
in the auditorium,
in the theater, screaming,

21:11.687 --> 21:14.773
"Arnold! Arnold! Arnold!"

21:14.856 --> 21:17.067
[audience chanting] Arnold!

21:17.150 --> 21:18.443
[Arnold] I saw the fantasy,

21:18.944 --> 21:20.362
and it's not a dream.

21:21.029 --> 21:23.782
I said, "No, fuck the dream.
What are you gonna do with a dream?"

21:23.865 --> 21:25.701
"You have to have a clear vision."

21:25.784 --> 21:28.412
And when you visualize something
really clearly,

21:28.495 --> 21:31.790
you believe that you 100% can get there.

21:34.543 --> 21:36.169
My very first impression was

21:36.253 --> 21:39.881
this is the most outstanding junior
I ever saw in my life,

21:40.465 --> 21:42.092
because he had it all.

21:42.175 --> 21:47.306
He had a kind of charisma
very unusual for that age.

21:48.015 --> 21:49.266
He owned the stage

21:49.349 --> 21:50.309
already then.

21:50.976 --> 21:54.146
I talked to him,
"What do you think to come to Munich

21:54.229 --> 21:56.023
as trainer in the gym I manage?"

22:05.615 --> 22:08.702
[Arnold] I was supposed to be
in the military for three years.

22:08.785 --> 22:11.330
So I had to ask if I can leave early.

22:13.081 --> 22:15.083
That position that was offered to me

22:15.167 --> 22:18.420
to become a trainer
in a bodybuilding gym in Germany,

22:18.503 --> 22:19.588
was very appealing.

22:19.671 --> 22:22.591
And it was kind of really
the only solution

22:22.674 --> 22:26.261
to get me out of Austria
and one step closer to America.

22:27.846 --> 22:29.222
You're not gonna go and become

22:29.306 --> 22:31.308
the greatest bodybuilder of all time
in Austria,

22:31.391 --> 22:34.936
because you need to train
with the best bodybuilders around you,

22:35.020 --> 22:37.647
and the mecca of bodybuilding was America.

22:39.316 --> 22:42.819
"I got to get out of here,
no matter what it takes."

22:42.903 --> 22:44.696
[train horn blows]

22:50.327 --> 22:52.662
[Arnold] I don't look at it as,
"Oh my God."

22:53.330 --> 22:56.333
"What a terrible upbringing I had."

22:56.917 --> 22:57.751
No.

22:58.251 --> 23:01.755
What I hated as a kid was good,

23:01.838 --> 23:04.674
because that's what drove me
to get out of there.

23:10.222 --> 23:12.224
All right, let's feed the girls.

23:13.517 --> 23:15.060
Uno, Misty!

23:18.146 --> 23:19.689
Uno, Misty!

23:19.773 --> 23:21.691
I could train longer than anyone else.

23:21.775 --> 23:25.320
I could go through misery
when I traveled to other countries.

23:25.404 --> 23:27.989
I was able to do things
that others couldn't do

23:28.073 --> 23:29.199
because of that.

23:29.282 --> 23:31.493
Ah, pushing him out of the way.

23:32.119 --> 23:33.495
It didn't bother me,

23:33.578 --> 23:36.206
because it was better
than where I came from.

23:36.706 --> 23:38.708
[energetic music plays]

23:40.752 --> 23:42.963
[Arnold] When I arrived in Munich,

23:43.630 --> 23:46.675
my friend Albert Busek
picked me up from the train station,

23:47.717 --> 23:49.636
and I moved into the gym.

23:50.762 --> 23:52.764
There was a tiny little room,

23:52.848 --> 23:56.268
and my bed maybe was as big
as the bed that I grew up with.

23:56.893 --> 24:01.648
All I had was a mixer
that helped me mix my protein drinks

24:01.731 --> 24:02.649
and a few clothes.

24:02.732 --> 24:03.567
That was it.

24:04.359 --> 24:07.446
And I stayed there for at least a year.

24:08.697 --> 24:10.782
So, at any given time,

24:10.866 --> 24:12.617
I can go out and work out.

24:14.494 --> 24:19.458
I mean, how lucky of a son of a bitch am I
to have the gym be my home?

24:20.959 --> 24:23.545
I then developed my own little family,

24:23.628 --> 24:25.505
which was Albert Busek

24:25.589 --> 24:27.382
and Franco Columbu,

24:27.466 --> 24:29.843
who I met the year before in Stuttgart.

24:30.510 --> 24:32.220
He was the perfect training partner,

24:32.304 --> 24:36.391
and he was one of the very few Italians
that spoke German.

24:37.267 --> 24:39.686
[Franco] He comes from Austria.
I came from Italy.

24:39.769 --> 24:42.647
And we started training together
and having fun.

24:43.940 --> 24:46.443
Since then,
I'm one of Arnold's best friends.

24:46.526 --> 24:47.694
I messed it up.

24:47.777 --> 24:48.904
Say that again.

24:49.446 --> 24:51.490
♪ Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa ♪

24:51.573 --> 24:52.782
♪ Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa ♪

24:54.784 --> 24:56.411
♪ Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa… ♪

24:56.495 --> 24:59.706
[Arnold] My friends helped me
to raise money for an airline ticket

24:59.789 --> 25:02.042
to compete in the Mr. Universe contest.

25:03.543 --> 25:05.754
♪ Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa
Whoa, whoa, whoa ♪

25:08.924 --> 25:10.675
[Arnold] So imagine,
just a few months before,

25:10.759 --> 25:12.052
you're in the military.

25:12.135 --> 25:16.264
And now you're traveling to London
to go to the Mr. Universe contest.

25:16.973 --> 25:20.477
My goal was to place in the top six,

25:21.102 --> 25:22.729
but I placed second

25:22.812 --> 25:24.189
with the age of 19.

25:24.814 --> 25:26.358
I said, "Oh my God."

25:26.858 --> 25:28.568
"If I'm winning second

25:28.652 --> 25:32.739
as this little farm boy from Austria
that has no experience,

25:32.822 --> 25:34.241
next year I'm gonna win!"

25:34.824 --> 25:37.077
[Albert] Arnold was so gifted

25:37.160 --> 25:39.621
that regular people,
the fans of bodybuilding, knew

25:39.704 --> 25:41.248
this is the future.

25:45.627 --> 25:47.712
[Arnold] At the Mr. Universe competition,

25:47.796 --> 25:52.509
one of the judges was a man
by the name of Wag Bennett.

25:53.468 --> 25:54.302
And he'd say…

25:54.386 --> 25:57.389
[imitating Wag] "Arnold,
you look fantastic. You look fantastic."

25:57.472 --> 25:59.057
"It's absolutely marvelous."

25:59.140 --> 26:01.476
All this British stuff, right?

26:03.270 --> 26:05.480
He invited us to a dinner,

26:05.564 --> 26:09.317
and he's a judge, so I thought,
"This is so unbelievable."

26:09.401 --> 26:12.112
My English was terrible then,

26:12.195 --> 26:14.322
so we always were laughing about it.

26:16.199 --> 26:20.370
Wag then said to me, "Well, if you ever
come back, you can stay with us."

26:20.453 --> 26:22.455
"You don't have to stay in a hotel."

26:23.498 --> 26:24.416
The next year,

26:25.166 --> 26:27.752
Wag organized the competition

26:27.836 --> 26:30.922
and he paid for the airline ticket
to fly over there.

26:32.674 --> 26:35.176
So I was at the Bennett's house in London,

26:35.260 --> 26:37.304
on 335 Romford Road.

26:37.387 --> 26:38.763
I remember it exactly.

26:38.847 --> 26:40.932
And in walked Reg Park.

26:47.272 --> 26:48.898
Meeting Reg Park

26:49.608 --> 26:52.902
was, like,
one of those extraordinary moments.

26:56.489 --> 26:58.491
You see him in magazines.

26:59.117 --> 27:00.910
You see him in movies.

27:01.494 --> 27:03.455
And then all of a sudden, there he is.

27:05.749 --> 27:09.085
He just came from South Africa
and he wants to work out.

27:09.586 --> 27:11.755
And then we're working out together.

27:13.256 --> 27:17.469
I remember that he didn't even…
he didn't even take off his sweater.

27:20.930 --> 27:24.768
And it was just extraordinary
to see Hercules

27:25.477 --> 27:28.438
that you saw in the movies,
to see him in front of you,

27:28.521 --> 27:31.858
and then to have a conversation
and to have him be so nice.

27:31.941 --> 27:34.069
He knew everything about me,

27:34.152 --> 27:36.112
because Wag Bennett told him.

27:40.909 --> 27:43.203
To really motivate me, he said to me,

27:43.286 --> 27:45.497
"If you win the Mr. Universe contest,

27:45.580 --> 27:47.957
I'm gonna bring you down to South Africa."

27:48.041 --> 27:49.834
"And I'm gonna have you
do posing exhibitions."

27:49.918 --> 27:51.920
I'm gonna pay
you for each positing exhibition."

27:52.003 --> 27:55.965
"You can make some money there,
and you're gonna see the entire country."

27:56.049 --> 27:57.634
[adventurous music plays]

27:59.678 --> 28:01.554
[Arnold] There's no room for mistakes,

28:01.638 --> 28:04.432
because I have to be Mr. Universe in 1967.

28:07.018 --> 28:09.396
Wag would say,
"You gotta train your calves."

28:09.479 --> 28:13.274
"Your biceps are much larger
than your calves."

28:13.983 --> 28:16.695
"The calves are skinny,
and the whole proportion is off."

28:18.029 --> 28:19.280
If you want to win,

28:19.364 --> 28:22.742
you need to be fine-tuned
and you have to have everything at ten.

28:23.702 --> 28:25.704
[crowd cheering]

28:27.497 --> 28:29.499
Finally, it all came together.

28:31.960 --> 28:33.169
[announcer] And the winner,

28:34.421 --> 28:35.880
Arnold Schwarzenegger!

28:40.927 --> 28:42.303
[Arnold] At the age of 20,

28:42.929 --> 28:44.681
I made my vision

28:44.764 --> 28:45.890
become a reality.

28:47.976 --> 28:51.312
On that very same stage
that Reg Park won it,

28:52.105 --> 28:55.859
and I got exactly the same trophy
that he got.

28:55.942 --> 28:58.653
And exactly the way I envisioned it.

28:59.571 --> 29:01.364
All the people were screaming.

29:01.448 --> 29:02.824
[crowd chanting] Arnold!

29:02.907 --> 29:05.994
[Arnold] I felt like,
"This is like a fairy tale."

29:06.494 --> 29:08.455
Everything falls into place.

29:25.680 --> 29:28.892
Reg Park invites me to Johannesburg

29:30.477 --> 29:31.728
to stay in his house.

29:33.646 --> 29:35.315
Do you know what that did to me?

29:35.398 --> 29:39.194
I'm getting invited by my idol
to go to his home turf.

29:41.780 --> 29:43.698
[man] I met Arnold when he came here.

29:43.782 --> 29:46.117
I was, uh, nine at the time.

29:46.201 --> 29:48.745
He was very polite. He was well-mannered.

29:49.245 --> 29:51.956
He would wear sandals and socks, you know?

29:52.040 --> 29:54.459
Like a country bumpkin, so to speak.

29:54.959 --> 29:58.713
Lily-white skin.
Everybody on the beach had a tan.

29:59.464 --> 30:02.717
I remember him almost being in awe,

30:02.801 --> 30:05.178
but my dad made him feel so comfortable.

30:05.261 --> 30:08.890
My mother, you know, of course,
made him feel so comfortable as well.

30:08.973 --> 30:10.934
He immediately became part of the family.

30:11.017 --> 30:14.437
We'd go out to meals together every night
and go to movies.

30:14.938 --> 30:19.317
What he really learned from my parents
was how important family was.

30:20.068 --> 30:23.029
I think that impressed him
more than anything else.

30:24.656 --> 30:27.116
My mother gave Arnold some pointers.

30:27.200 --> 30:31.037
You know, he could do the basic poses,
but there was no flow and transition.

30:31.120 --> 30:34.082
So she helped him
put his routine together.

30:35.667 --> 30:37.794
[Arnold] Mareon was a ballet teacher.

30:38.461 --> 30:41.965
She taught Reg
how to be more graceful on stage.

30:42.757 --> 30:46.427
You couldn't get more two opposites.
Ballet is all about grace.

30:47.512 --> 30:50.056
Then you have bodybuilding,
which is kind of blocky

30:50.139 --> 30:51.766
and not much movement.

30:53.518 --> 30:55.103
I didn't understand it all,

30:55.186 --> 31:00.108
but then, as time went on,
I started utilizing what she taught me.

31:05.697 --> 31:07.365
When I was a kid, I was shy,

31:08.199 --> 31:10.201
and bodybuilding

31:10.785 --> 31:13.454
was a sport where you had to perform.

31:13.538 --> 31:15.832
So I could learn it in my own way,

31:15.915 --> 31:17.834
to perform and to pose on stage.

31:17.917 --> 31:21.045
And people then correct you and say,
you know, "Smile more when you perform,"

31:21.129 --> 31:22.088
And do this and do that.

31:22.171 --> 31:24.465
This is how it slowly came about

31:24.549 --> 31:26.217
to become an entertainer

31:26.301 --> 31:29.095
and really enjoying the moment.

31:31.431 --> 31:36.728
In 1968, I went and competed
at the Mr. Universe contest in London.

31:36.811 --> 31:38.813
Every time they called out a pose…

31:38.897 --> 31:42.692
If I did a double bicep pose,
I had the biggest biceps.

31:43.568 --> 31:46.279
Then, when we turned around
and do a back pose,

31:46.362 --> 31:49.198
there's no one that's going to have
this kind of a back.

31:50.783 --> 31:52.785
So I knew I'm gonna win.

31:52.869 --> 31:54.871
[triumphant music plays]

32:01.294 --> 32:05.965
I win the second Mr. Universe title.
I feel, like, at an all-time high.

32:06.841 --> 32:09.594
And I'm about to go back to Munich,

32:09.677 --> 32:11.721
when I get a telegram

32:11.804 --> 32:12.805
from Joe Weider.

32:14.015 --> 32:15.892
I said to myself, "Oh my God."

32:15.975 --> 32:19.854
"Joe Weider?
He's like the godfather of bodybuilding."

32:20.688 --> 32:23.691
The trainer of champions since 1939.

32:24.233 --> 32:26.945
All of the guys that win
Mr. Universe and Mr. World,

32:27.028 --> 32:28.696
they have been trained by Joe Weider.

32:28.780 --> 32:30.615
And it says in the telegram,

32:30.698 --> 32:34.744
"I'm inviting you to come to Miami
to our Mr. Universe competition,"

32:34.827 --> 32:36.287
because there was two.

32:36.371 --> 32:39.415
Weider started a Mr. Universe
in the 60s in America.

32:41.000 --> 32:44.545
I didn't go back home.
I didn't pick up any of my belongings.

32:45.296 --> 32:48.925
I called Albert
and I called Franco and said, "Look."

32:49.008 --> 32:52.512
"I just got an invitation from Weider.
I'm not coming back."

32:52.595 --> 32:54.347
"I'm gonna move to America."

32:54.430 --> 32:55.598
"Bye-bye."

32:55.682 --> 32:57.684
["I Got the Feelin'" plays]

32:59.811 --> 33:02.105
♪ Uh-huh, uh, uh ♪

33:02.188 --> 33:03.940
♪ I got the feelin' ♪

33:04.482 --> 33:05.316
[wheels squeal]

33:05.400 --> 33:07.193
♪ Hey! ♪

33:08.569 --> 33:09.529
♪ All right ♪

33:10.071 --> 33:10.947
♪ Ow ♪

33:11.781 --> 33:12.615
♪ Hey… ♪

33:15.201 --> 33:17.620
When I came to America, I felt like…

33:18.997 --> 33:19.872
[sighs]

33:22.250 --> 33:23.751
…finally, I'm in my home.

33:24.252 --> 33:26.129
♪ Baby, baby, baby… ♪

33:26.212 --> 33:28.339
Then we got flew down to Florida.

33:28.423 --> 33:30.008
♪ Baby, baby, baby ♪

33:30.091 --> 33:31.426
♪ Baby ♪

33:31.509 --> 33:32.468
♪ Come on now ♪

33:32.552 --> 33:34.345
[Arnold] I was absolutely convinced

33:34.429 --> 33:36.764
that I'm gonna beat
all the American bodybuilders.

33:36.848 --> 33:39.392
Set me up as kind of, like,
the new champion.

33:39.475 --> 33:42.103
Become the greatest bodybuilder
of all times.

33:42.895 --> 33:47.442
He was acting so arrogant and cocky
like the winner, but he wasn't in shape,

33:48.026 --> 33:51.237
because it was all about being big
and, you know, size with him.

33:52.280 --> 33:55.950
[Arnold] And when they announced
the fourth place, third place,

33:56.034 --> 33:58.995
and the second place,
Arnold Schwarzenegger.

34:00.830 --> 34:02.290
Oh, fuck.

34:03.374 --> 34:04.834
This can't be.

34:08.046 --> 34:12.884
I once was considered the unbeatable guy,
and now, all of a sudden, Frank Zane won.

34:14.635 --> 34:17.096
This is terrible. I'm embarrassed.

34:19.766 --> 34:22.602
[Frank] I think he was just
used to winning all the time.

34:22.685 --> 34:26.230
Landing in this country the first time,
getting defeated

34:26.314 --> 34:27.732
by, as his words,

34:27.815 --> 34:30.485
"a chicken with 17-inch arms,"

34:30.568 --> 34:32.403
that really bothered him.

34:35.865 --> 34:37.867
[Arnold] I was so devastated.

34:37.950 --> 34:40.411
I was lying there
in the middle of the night in bed

34:40.495 --> 34:42.205
in this hotel room,

34:42.288 --> 34:44.457
and I thought the world
is coming to an end.

34:47.877 --> 34:49.670
I'm in a strange country.

34:49.754 --> 34:51.589
I cannot communicate here.

34:51.672 --> 34:53.925
I'm thousands of miles away from home.

34:54.550 --> 34:56.344
And I just lost.

34:56.427 --> 34:58.429
I just disappointed everybody.

35:00.014 --> 35:02.683
So in my mind, the bodybuilding world
was going to say,

35:02.767 --> 35:05.686
"Schwarzenegger is not
what we thought he is."

35:05.770 --> 35:06.771
"So fuck him."

35:08.397 --> 35:10.024
I cried the whole night.

35:16.322 --> 35:18.741
The next day, I said, "Okay."

35:18.825 --> 35:21.369
"You cried like a little baby,
you asshole."

35:21.452 --> 35:22.995
"And now, let's move on."

35:25.873 --> 35:29.544
And then Weider gave me an airline ticket
to go to Los Angeles.

35:30.586 --> 35:34.257
He's gonna take care of things
and he's gonna get me an apartment.

35:36.342 --> 35:40.012
I wrote to my friends right away.
I said, "This is quite different."

35:40.930 --> 35:43.307
I felt, like, totally helpless

35:43.391 --> 35:44.475
and alone.

35:47.019 --> 35:49.188
The gyms that I went to

35:49.272 --> 35:52.358
were gyms where
the best bodybuilders worked out.

35:52.441 --> 35:54.694
I come in there and I want to work out.

35:54.777 --> 35:58.197
And there's guys that owned the gym,
like, Vince Gironda,

35:58.281 --> 35:59.740
he owned Vince's Gym.

35:59.824 --> 36:01.951
He says, "You're still a baby."

36:02.034 --> 36:04.704
"We have to get rid of
a lot of fat on you,

36:04.787 --> 36:06.789
but you have a lot of potential."

36:06.873 --> 36:10.543
And I said to myself, "What the fuck
is he talking about? Potential?"

36:12.128 --> 36:14.005
Then I trained at Gold's Gym,

36:14.088 --> 36:17.425
and Joe Gold immediately called me
"Balloon Belly."

36:17.508 --> 36:18.843
I said,

36:19.594 --> 36:20.511
"Jesus."

36:22.180 --> 36:25.892
I realized why it was so important
to come to America,

36:25.975 --> 36:28.686
because they just have
a whole different understanding

36:28.769 --> 36:30.688
of what it means being in shape.

36:31.772 --> 36:34.859
I alone cannot accomplish anything.

36:36.527 --> 36:37.778
I need help.

36:39.155 --> 36:43.743
So I invited Frank Zane,
the guy that I was beaten by,

36:43.826 --> 36:45.786
to come out to California

36:45.870 --> 36:47.121
and to train with me,

36:47.205 --> 36:49.123
because I wanted to see firsthand

36:49.207 --> 36:52.418
what does he do to get
this kind of a quality of a physique.

36:52.919 --> 36:55.838
And I stayed with him
on a cot in his living room,

36:55.922 --> 36:58.090
and we'd go to the gym and train.

36:58.174 --> 37:01.385
Go to the beach. Take pictures for Weider.

37:01.469 --> 37:03.429
I went back to Florida

37:03.512 --> 37:06.682
and resigned my teaching position
and moved to California.

37:06.766 --> 37:08.851
[Arnold] And then,
when I was training here,

37:08.935 --> 37:10.937
especially in Gold's Gym, I felt like,

37:11.020 --> 37:14.899
"Wouldn't it be great
if Franco would see what's going on here?"

37:14.982 --> 37:19.153
I mean, he was my close friend
and training partner in Munich.

37:19.237 --> 37:20.446
I really missed him.

37:20.529 --> 37:24.325
But when Weider heard what his height was,
he had no interest at all.

37:24.408 --> 37:27.662
So he kept saying, "No, I don't want
to bring over a little guy like that."

37:27.745 --> 37:28.579
"Come on."

37:29.163 --> 37:32.166
And then eventually Artie Zeller,
the photographer, and I,

37:32.250 --> 37:33.918
we kind of convinced him.

37:34.001 --> 37:36.963
And from then,
I mean, everything really picked up.

37:37.046 --> 37:40.174
Cinque, sei, sette.

37:40.258 --> 37:41.759
-[groans]
-[Arnold] What?

37:41.842 --> 37:42.802
Sette.

37:43.427 --> 37:44.470
Otto.

37:45.179 --> 37:46.013
Nove.

37:47.098 --> 37:47.974
Dieci.

37:48.766 --> 37:50.059
-[laughs]
-[Arnold] Okay.

37:50.142 --> 37:51.394
-That's hard.
-[Franco] I get it.

37:51.477 --> 37:53.271
-I get it.
-[Arnold] Oh, Franco gets it.

37:55.481 --> 37:57.817
-Okay, pick it up.
-[both laughing]

37:57.900 --> 38:00.778
[Arnold] In that area
of building a community,

38:00.861 --> 38:03.489
the talent of mine was actually better

38:03.572 --> 38:05.700
than my talent in bodybuilding.

38:05.783 --> 38:07.910
["California Soul" plays]

38:10.079 --> 38:12.373
[Arnold] Gold's Gym in Venice Beach.

38:12.456 --> 38:16.294
Bodybuilders training for championships
went there to train.

38:16.377 --> 38:18.379
♪ Like a sound you hear
That lingers in your ear ♪

38:18.462 --> 38:19.463
♪ But you can't forget… ♪

38:19.547 --> 38:23.009
[Arnold] And then Joe Weider publicized it
as the champions' gym.

38:23.092 --> 38:25.678
-[man] That nose will look skinny now.
-[laughing]

38:25.761 --> 38:30.391
My first impression of him
was he was outgoing, funny,

38:30.474 --> 38:32.268
and always cracking jokes.

38:32.351 --> 38:35.062
When he was in the gym, he was focused.

38:35.146 --> 38:37.606
♪ California soul… ♪

38:41.152 --> 38:43.612
[Frank] It was all energy,
and we helped each other.

38:44.363 --> 38:47.199
Now, Arnold was a great person to have
in the gym when you're working out,

38:47.283 --> 38:49.577
because just his presence made you
want to work out harder

38:49.660 --> 38:50.870
just to impress him.

38:51.412 --> 38:52.872
He was a perfectionist.

38:54.498 --> 38:56.250
[Arnold] You train together,
help each other.

38:56.334 --> 38:59.462
You even help each other
pumping up backstage with the towels,

38:59.545 --> 39:00.880
and you oil each other up.

39:00.963 --> 39:03.132
You put the oil on me
because I cannot reach in the back.

39:03.215 --> 39:05.134
Someone has to put the oil on my back.

39:05.217 --> 39:07.178
That's what you do. You help each other.

39:07.261 --> 39:09.805
And then before you go out,
you say, "Good luck."

39:09.889 --> 39:12.433
I used to say, "Good luck,"
and "I'm going to beat you."

39:12.516 --> 39:16.020
♪ Soul… ♪

39:16.854 --> 39:19.523
[Arnold] I was never a fanatic about diet.

39:19.607 --> 39:22.610
It was Frank Zane and Franco Columbu

39:22.693 --> 39:24.403
who put my vitamins together.

39:25.029 --> 39:27.740
And then we would experiment
with steroids.

39:28.282 --> 39:31.577
Everybody in the bodybuilding field
who is up there on the top

39:31.660 --> 39:33.287
is taking steroids.

39:35.164 --> 39:39.835
Maybe five percent of my progress

39:39.919 --> 39:41.253
is from the steroids.

39:42.046 --> 39:43.923
I had doctor's supervision.

39:44.006 --> 39:48.094
You stayed with a very strict rule
of doing it four months a year

39:48.177 --> 39:50.346
before a competition, and then lay off.

39:51.555 --> 39:53.974
So I changed my eating habits
and everything.

39:54.683 --> 39:55.976
I got really tanned.

39:56.560 --> 40:00.564
If your whole personality is to show off,

40:01.315 --> 40:03.859
you can't wait
to show people what you have.

40:03.943 --> 40:07.321
There were hundreds of people
watching guys work out.

40:07.405 --> 40:09.824
♪ California soul… ♪

40:09.907 --> 40:12.618
[Arnold] I felt like I was living
in the middle of a circus.

40:13.661 --> 40:16.622
So you were getting it all times,

40:16.705 --> 40:19.208
the satisfaction of people watching you

40:19.792 --> 40:22.294
and saying, "Wow, he looks incredible."

40:24.255 --> 40:25.256
♪ Just gimme, yeah ♪

40:25.339 --> 40:26.549
♪ Just gimme, yeah ♪

40:27.299 --> 40:29.176
♪ Oh, it's all a trend ♪

40:32.012 --> 40:34.432
[woman] It was the summer of '69.

40:35.182 --> 40:37.852
I was working as a hostess
at Zucky's Deli.

40:39.311 --> 40:42.231
He came over to me and he said,

40:42.314 --> 40:44.066
"You are so sexy."

40:44.150 --> 40:46.402
"I need to ask you out on a date."

40:47.653 --> 40:49.947
With a really thick accent.

40:50.030 --> 40:52.533
Barely 100 words in his vocabulary.

40:53.409 --> 40:56.412
He was handsome. He was magnetic.

40:56.495 --> 40:57.872
He was charismatic.

40:58.622 --> 41:00.624
He was just different.

41:02.918 --> 41:06.630
When he arrived for our date,
I was watching the moon landing.

41:07.548 --> 41:09.133
[man over radio] We copy it down, Eagle.

41:09.216 --> 41:10.259
[indistinct radio chatter]

41:10.342 --> 41:14.221
So we watched it together.
We took photos in front of the television.

41:14.305 --> 41:16.849
[man 2 over radio] Tranquility base here.
The eagle has landed.

41:17.391 --> 41:18.851
[Barbara] After our first date,

41:18.934 --> 41:21.645
we saw each other
all the time that we could.

41:22.771 --> 41:25.441
He created laughter everywhere.

41:25.524 --> 41:26.775
He was just so

41:27.943 --> 41:29.028
mesmerizing.

41:31.614 --> 41:34.116
[Arnold] Barbara was the first time

41:34.200 --> 41:39.497
that I saw, through her,
kind of how America celebrates Christmas,

41:39.997 --> 41:42.041
because she would take me home,

41:42.124 --> 41:44.793
and the family would just be so inclusive.

41:45.753 --> 41:47.213
It was the first time

41:47.796 --> 41:50.674
in my life
that I ever celebrated a birthday,

41:50.758 --> 41:53.260
when Barbara's mother made
a birthday cake.

41:54.929 --> 41:58.098
I never got a cake. No one ever sang
"Happy Birthday" or anything.

41:58.182 --> 41:59.225
I don't know why.

42:01.185 --> 42:04.688
It gave me another way
of really appreciating

42:04.772 --> 42:06.607
the American way of life,

42:07.107 --> 42:08.859
and to have a normal life.

42:10.444 --> 42:11.862
But with my family…

42:11.946 --> 42:15.282
The communication with my parents
was not good.

42:16.909 --> 42:18.077
And my brother…

42:18.160 --> 42:21.872
I kind of erased him out of my mind

42:21.956 --> 42:24.750
for years during my bodybuilding years.

42:26.835 --> 42:30.214
I felt like I was creating
my own life over here,

42:30.297 --> 42:33.175
and I wanted nothing to do
with my past life.

42:37.888 --> 42:41.517
Joe Weider was interested in trying
to figure out how does he sell me.

42:41.600 --> 42:43.519
So he came up with this idea

42:44.019 --> 42:46.188
that I'm this German machine.

42:47.189 --> 42:49.608
No emotions, just marching forward,

42:49.692 --> 42:52.194
and it's going to make me the champion.

42:52.820 --> 42:55.197
And I loved it,
because that's what I saw myself,

42:55.281 --> 42:57.575
as someone that couldn't be stopped.

43:01.704 --> 43:06.917
Joe Weider had one goal in mind,
and that is that I win every competition.

43:07.001 --> 43:09.461
That I'm on the cover of his magazine.

43:09.545 --> 43:12.965
That I sell a shitload
of food supplements for him.

43:13.549 --> 43:15.843
And that everything that I did,

43:15.926 --> 43:18.554
he would use the name Weider for it.

43:18.637 --> 43:20.764
So when I came up with

43:20.848 --> 43:23.851
splitting my bicep training
with my tricep training,

43:23.934 --> 43:26.312
he called it The Weider Split Routine.

43:27.229 --> 43:28.647
So that was the deal.

43:29.481 --> 43:31.191
I'm just gonna go over this.

43:31.275 --> 43:34.403
You should have
unique pictures taken, Arnold.

43:34.486 --> 43:35.988
Make it look different.

43:36.071 --> 43:37.906
I had to go and work with him and say,

43:37.990 --> 43:41.493
"Joe, you're selling your products.
You're making millions of dollars."

43:41.577 --> 43:44.288
"I want to also sell
some products of mine."

43:44.371 --> 43:48.292
"All I need from you is give me
advertisement space in your magazine."

43:49.793 --> 43:53.422
I wanted to make money
and I wanted to turn one dollar into two.

43:53.505 --> 43:56.800
And I wanted to learn how to do that
in America the American way.

43:56.884 --> 43:58.344
I said to Joe Weider,

43:58.427 --> 44:01.055
"Can you help me?
I want to go to college to learn English."

44:01.138 --> 44:02.973
"Then I wanna take some business classes,

44:03.057 --> 44:05.934
because eventually
I may have to take over your operation."

44:06.018 --> 44:07.269
And he loved that.

44:07.895 --> 44:09.396
These are the new covers.

44:10.230 --> 44:11.398
[Arnold] Let me see it.

44:12.066 --> 44:14.652
We don't want to put him on the cover.
Come on, Joe.

44:14.735 --> 44:16.779
You told me one time
that you're only putting

44:16.862 --> 44:19.490
Mr. Universes or Mr. Olympias
on the cover.

44:19.573 --> 44:20.616
[Joe] Five more copies…

44:20.699 --> 44:21.533
[Arnold] Joe?

44:26.705 --> 44:28.707
[breathing deeply]

44:52.981 --> 44:55.192
[Arnold] Every time I want anything,

44:55.275 --> 44:58.362
I say to myself,
"Okay, now what's the next thing?"

44:59.071 --> 45:02.282
If you're always hungry,
you're never really satisfied.

45:04.326 --> 45:07.413
Because Reg Park, of course,
won three Mr. Universe contests,

45:07.496 --> 45:09.415
Arnold has to break that record.

45:12.418 --> 45:16.380
When people think, "This is too much."
For me, it was definitely not enough.

45:16.463 --> 45:18.215
And then I wanted more.

45:18.298 --> 45:20.300
[suspenseful music plays]

45:21.885 --> 45:23.429
[Jon Jon] My dad had retired,

45:23.929 --> 45:27.057
but he decided to compete in Mr. Universe.

45:28.600 --> 45:31.270
At that time, my dad was 42.

45:31.353 --> 45:33.063
Arnold was 23.

45:33.147 --> 45:36.024
[Arnold] Someone told me, "Do you know
who else is competing this year?"

45:36.108 --> 45:37.025
And I say, "Who?"

45:37.109 --> 45:38.527
They said, "Reg Park."

45:38.610 --> 45:40.863
I said, "Come on. This is impossible."

45:42.114 --> 45:44.908
I felt kind of weird
to compete against my idol.

45:50.497 --> 45:51.832
And then won.

45:54.585 --> 45:58.130
When that happened, it was something
really weird that happened mentally to me.

45:59.047 --> 46:00.674
I felt guilty somewhat.

46:01.258 --> 46:02.551
That my ego got in the way

46:02.634 --> 46:04.845
or maybe I shouldn't have competed
that year.

46:08.307 --> 46:12.227
To know that, as a 15-year-old kid,
you were dreaming about that

46:12.311 --> 46:13.854
and you were idolizing it.

46:15.063 --> 46:17.608
And now, all of a sudden,
you become the one

46:17.691 --> 46:19.234
that others are idolizing.

46:21.028 --> 46:23.781
I made this vision become a reality.

46:34.333 --> 46:37.377
My mind is just geared differently.

46:37.461 --> 46:39.671
You know,
it's geared towards moving forward.

46:39.755 --> 46:41.715
[magical music plays]

46:41.799 --> 46:43.801
[wind blowing gently]

46:45.260 --> 46:46.845
[Arnold] What is the new thing?

46:48.597 --> 46:51.558
A new challenge. A new mountain to climb.

46:56.647 --> 46:59.441
Mr. Universe
is a world championship title,

46:59.525 --> 47:01.610
but every year there's a Mr. Universe.

47:01.693 --> 47:03.362
But who is really, then, the best?

47:03.445 --> 47:05.405
[upbeat music plays]

47:05.489 --> 47:07.950
[Arnold]
So Joe Weider created the Mr. Olympia,

47:08.534 --> 47:11.328
where all the Mr. Universes
and all the world champions

47:11.411 --> 47:13.205
competes in the Mr. Olympia.

47:15.165 --> 47:18.210
If you win that,
then you can call yourself the best.

47:18.293 --> 47:19.294
Pow!

47:19.378 --> 47:20.712
Mr. Olympia!

47:22.756 --> 47:26.176
The year 1969,
that was my first Mr. Olympia.

47:26.802 --> 47:28.345
It was a different league.

47:29.638 --> 47:31.890
I competed against Sergio Oliva.

47:32.599 --> 47:33.934
I lost against him.

47:34.017 --> 47:35.853
He was better than me.

47:36.854 --> 47:39.064
I gave him a big kiss on stage,

47:39.565 --> 47:42.276
and I said,
"Enjoy it, because this is the last time."

47:44.111 --> 47:46.864
The next year I came back with vengeance.

47:46.947 --> 47:49.658
I had to kind of make him the villain,

47:50.409 --> 47:53.120
to go and train harder
and harder and harder.

47:53.203 --> 47:56.039
I finally got the chance to confront him.

48:00.502 --> 48:02.379
I then pulled a little trick on him.

48:03.839 --> 48:06.049
We were doing pose-off after pose-off.

48:06.133 --> 48:08.260
And then I said to him,
"I think it's enough."

48:08.343 --> 48:10.053
"I think they must know by now

48:10.137 --> 48:11.597
who is going to be the winner."

48:11.680 --> 48:14.474
He says, "You're right,"
and then he walked off.

48:15.767 --> 48:18.687
And then I pointed at him,
like, "He's giving up."

48:19.646 --> 48:21.940
So it was like
a psychological little trick

48:22.024 --> 48:23.859
to kind of close the deal
once and for all.

48:23.942 --> 48:25.736
[cheering and applause]

48:26.570 --> 48:29.823
He turned around and said,
"You son of a bitch."

48:29.907 --> 48:32.159
[chuckles]
He was, like, really pissed off about it.

48:35.120 --> 48:37.122
["Super Guy (Flying High)" plays]

48:37.915 --> 48:42.377
[Arnold] In the '70s, I kept being driven
to go from title to title.

48:47.132 --> 48:50.802
I was so far ahead of everybody else
that I ran over everybody.

48:50.886 --> 48:52.971
♪ Super guy ♪

48:53.055 --> 48:54.306
♪ What will you be ♪

48:54.389 --> 48:56.892
♪ When your cloud falls ♪

48:56.975 --> 48:58.018
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

48:58.101 --> 49:00.062
♪ Hey, super guy ♪

49:00.145 --> 49:02.314
♪ What your mama say? ♪

49:02.397 --> 49:04.816
♪ Oh ♪

49:04.900 --> 49:05.776
♪ Ow ♪

49:05.859 --> 49:08.111
♪ Hey, hey, super guy ♪

49:08.195 --> 49:09.988
♪ What you gonna do? ♪

49:18.580 --> 49:21.333
-[man] What do you expect to see tonight?
-[man 2] I'm not quite sure.

49:21.416 --> 49:23.543
I'm curious to see what it's…
what it looks like.

49:24.962 --> 49:26.630
[man 3] Can we ask
what you expect tonight?

49:26.713 --> 49:29.424
I expect to see fantastic bodybuilders.

49:29.508 --> 49:31.426
-[man 3] Have you ever been to one before?
-No.

49:31.510 --> 49:33.929
-[man 3] Have you ever been to one before?
-Never!

49:34.930 --> 49:36.014
-Have you?
-[man 3] Never.

49:36.098 --> 49:36.932
[laughs]

49:37.015 --> 49:39.017
[cheering]

49:49.152 --> 49:51.697
[Arnold] Being a bodybuilder
is like being an artist,

49:51.780 --> 49:54.825
being a sculptor
like Rodin or Michelangelo,

49:56.827 --> 50:01.623
because you have to have a sense
of symmetry and beauty.

50:01.707 --> 50:03.709
[applause]

50:05.335 --> 50:08.296
[Arnold] If you don't have that,
the whole thing together

50:08.380 --> 50:10.007
looks like a waste of time.

50:10.549 --> 50:12.342
[cheering]

50:18.140 --> 50:19.558
[man] That's it. Hold it.

50:19.641 --> 50:21.393
That's it. Just hold it.

50:21.476 --> 50:24.187
[man 2] Looks a little different
than two months ago, doesn't it?

50:24.813 --> 50:25.856
[exhales]

50:28.900 --> 50:31.528
[Arnold]
I never really was satisfied with my body.

50:31.611 --> 50:32.696
God almighty.

50:32.779 --> 50:37.117
I looked in the mirror and said to myself,
"I don't know how this shit body

50:37.200 --> 50:39.202
can ever win this competition."

50:40.996 --> 50:44.082
-Thanks for coming in.
-Lou Ferrigno is coming too.

50:45.542 --> 50:48.211
[Arnold] When I brag about myself,
that's all bullshit.

50:48.295 --> 50:50.422
-All right.
-Very dramatic, Arnold.

50:50.505 --> 50:52.466
[Arnold]
This is kind of like the other me,

50:52.549 --> 50:55.135
the me that I want the world to see.

50:55.218 --> 50:56.261
Take this one.

50:57.387 --> 51:00.474
That should inspire you,
because this is an arm shot.

51:02.017 --> 51:02.851
It's Columbu.

51:03.351 --> 51:04.394
How do you like that shot?

51:04.478 --> 51:06.563
[Arnold] But in reality,
when I'm by myself,

51:06.646 --> 51:08.607
I look at it and I say to myself,

51:08.690 --> 51:10.567
"It's not there yet. It's not happening."

51:10.650 --> 51:11.610
Check the chest.

51:12.277 --> 51:16.448
[Arnold] I think it's the very thing
that made me always be on the edge

51:16.531 --> 51:18.075
and always want more.

51:18.158 --> 51:20.577
Your chest looks tremendous, Arnold.

51:20.660 --> 51:21.620
Huge.

51:28.835 --> 51:32.714
I was in Baltimore and Philadelphia

51:32.798 --> 51:34.883
doing, uh, posing exhibitions.

51:34.966 --> 51:36.301
I came home,

51:37.594 --> 51:40.847
and, uh, Franco said to me…
He says, you know, "I have bad news."

51:41.807 --> 51:43.141
I said, "What's that?"

51:43.225 --> 51:46.686
He said to me… he says,
"Your brother died in a car accident."

51:47.187 --> 51:49.481
"He was drunk driving,

51:50.440 --> 51:54.736
and that he was hitting a telephone pole."

51:56.988 --> 51:58.740
And I was, like, stunned.

51:58.824 --> 52:00.367
[somber music plays]

52:06.206 --> 52:08.625
[Arnold]
He was always the darling of the family.

52:09.209 --> 52:10.836
He was very artistic.

52:10.919 --> 52:12.129
Very smart.

52:12.212 --> 52:13.547
Read a lot.

52:16.550 --> 52:19.928
But I don't think
my brother ever was really happy.

52:22.848 --> 52:27.936
I think he started drinking
because our upbringing was very tough.

52:28.603 --> 52:30.689
The brutality that was at home,

52:30.772 --> 52:33.775
the beatings that we got
from our parents sometimes,

52:33.859 --> 52:36.278
all of this, I think he could not sustain,

52:36.361 --> 52:37.279
that punishment.

52:37.362 --> 52:40.490
He was much more delicate of a person

52:40.574 --> 52:41.575
by nature.

52:43.618 --> 52:47.289
We had a very,
kind of, schizophrenic behavior

52:47.372 --> 52:49.583
that my brother and I witnessed at home.

52:49.666 --> 52:51.209
There was the kind father,

52:51.293 --> 52:55.046
and then there was the other times
where my father would come home drunk.

52:55.130 --> 52:58.133
And he would scream
at three in the morning.

52:58.216 --> 52:59.259
We would wake up,

52:59.885 --> 53:02.679
and, all of a sudden, you know,
our hearts were pounding,

53:03.972 --> 53:05.891
because we knew what that meant.

53:05.974 --> 53:08.977
That he could,
at any given time, strike my mother

53:09.060 --> 53:10.478
or go crazy.

53:10.562 --> 53:12.564
[indistinct yelling]

53:13.398 --> 53:16.484
So there was
this kind of strange violence.

53:16.943 --> 53:18.445
[birds chirping]

53:19.613 --> 53:22.407
The kind of upbringing that we had

53:22.908 --> 53:26.411
was beneficial for someone like me,

53:26.494 --> 53:29.706
who was, inside,
very strong and very determined.

53:30.498 --> 53:32.500
But my brother was more fragile.

53:34.961 --> 53:36.463
Nietzsche was right,

53:36.546 --> 53:40.217
that that what does not kill you,
will make you stronger.

53:40.300 --> 53:43.094
The very thing that made me who I am today

53:43.178 --> 53:46.014
was the very thing that destroyed him.

54:02.906 --> 54:04.658
[curious music plays]

54:04.741 --> 54:08.370
[Arnold] In 1972, when I was competing
in Essen, in Germany,

54:08.912 --> 54:11.206
my parents came for really

54:13.166 --> 54:14.668
unexplained reasons.

54:16.878 --> 54:19.130
I competed at least 50 times

54:19.214 --> 54:22.133
in weightlifting competitions,
in powerlifting competitions,

54:22.217 --> 54:25.095
in locals and in statewide competitions,

54:25.178 --> 54:26.554
national competitions.

54:26.638 --> 54:28.723
My parents never came to any of it.

54:28.807 --> 54:30.934
So that's why I was quite surprised.

54:34.396 --> 54:37.691
My father acted a little odd.

54:38.900 --> 54:43.071
He was a little slower.
He was sometimes slurring things.

54:43.154 --> 54:45.699
And so there was something off
a little bit there.

54:46.950 --> 54:48.034
A few weeks later,

54:49.119 --> 54:50.287
I got a phone call

54:50.870 --> 54:52.872
that my father had a stroke.

54:54.124 --> 54:57.294
I, uh, then took
the next flight to Austria

54:57.377 --> 54:59.754
and then went
to visit my father in the hospital.

55:00.255 --> 55:04.384
He was not able to communicate.

55:06.219 --> 55:08.138
You know,
he needed a lot of medical attention,

55:08.221 --> 55:11.683
but I did not know
is this something you can overcome or not.

55:11.766 --> 55:12.976
That I did not know.

55:15.729 --> 55:17.731
I flew back to Los Angeles,

55:18.523 --> 55:20.650
and then after that, he passed away.

55:22.444 --> 55:24.446
[somber music plays]

55:28.283 --> 55:30.452
[Arnold]
When my father and my brother died,

55:31.202 --> 55:33.830
I had no feelings about it.

55:33.913 --> 55:36.082
You know? I eliminated it.

55:36.791 --> 55:39.961
It maybe comes out
sometimes in my life later on…

55:40.045 --> 55:42.005
those feelings, you know,
but I don't know.

55:42.088 --> 55:44.507
I've been training myself to do that.

55:44.591 --> 55:47.677
Not to be affected by anything else
from the outside.

55:50.847 --> 55:51.931
I mean,

55:52.432 --> 55:53.808
I'm not an expert

55:54.476 --> 55:56.227
in psychology or anything like that.

55:56.311 --> 55:58.104
All I can tell you is that

55:59.856 --> 56:02.984
when you're a person
that has always a goal,

56:04.903 --> 56:06.446
that always has a mission,

56:07.614 --> 56:12.160
the less time that you have to think
about, "How do I feel today?"

56:12.660 --> 56:14.788
"Am I depressed today?"

56:15.372 --> 56:17.707
"Do I feel sorry for myself?"

56:17.791 --> 56:19.334
"Have I become a victim?"

56:19.959 --> 56:23.963
"Oh my God.
I feel so bad about myself," and all this.

56:24.047 --> 56:25.799
I don't have time for this crap.

56:25.882 --> 56:27.759
A lot of times,
it's people didn't work enough.

56:27.842 --> 56:29.761
If you're busy all the time,

56:29.844 --> 56:32.097
you don't have time
to think about this stuff.

56:32.180 --> 56:34.224
Let's just move forward.
Move. Move. Move. Move.

56:34.307 --> 56:36.559
["Lowdown" plays]

56:36.643 --> 56:40.313
[Arnold] When I realized
that bodybuilding is not established,

56:40.397 --> 56:43.149
